# Git first (step 0)

Before making **code or resource** changes in this workspace, ensure **`main`** (or the active branch) is current with **`origin`**: run **`git pull`** (or fetch + merge/rebase as the owner prefers) so the **laptop** checkout matches GitHub. **All dev is on one machine**; pull still avoids stale **`main`**, surprise merges, and “I thought that was already on **`origin`**” drift.

If **`git pull`** reports conflicts, resolve them **before** new edits. Shell-capable agents should **`git pull`** at session start when the task touches the repo.
